                                      26

                                                               N0597 = 94-0210
 
      8)  Motion (to disallow binding const volatile references to rvalues) by
          Adamczyk/Rumsby:
 
          Move we amend the sentence after the example in clause 8.5.3
          [dcl.init.ref] paragraph 6 from:
 
          Otherwise, the reference must be to a const type (i.e., cv1 must
          include const qualification); if not, the program is ill-formed.
 
          to:
 
          Otherwise, the reference must be to a non-volatile const type (i.e.,
          cv1 must be const); if not, the program is ill-formed.  For example,
 
          class X { ... };
